public interface XExpr<T extends XType>
extends XTerm<T>

Representation of an XExpr consisting of a an operator and one or more children that must be non-null. An XExpr can be used to represented a formula or field/method projection. In the case of projection the field/method information is encoded in the operator. Thus field projection will only have one child, the target: a.f would be encoded as (XLabeledOp(f) a).
